-- Hong Kong Stock Exchange Will Extend Trading Hours Starting in March 2011
-- B y   H a n n y   W a n
-- 2010-11-22T10:28:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-22/hong-kong-stock-exchange-to-extend-trading-hours-from-march.html
Hong Kong Exchanges & Clearing Ltd. ,
operator of Asia’s third-biggest stock market, said it will
extend its trading hours from March 7.  The city’s stock market will trade from 9:30 a.m. till
noon, and the afternoon session will run from 1:30 p.m. till 4
p.m. That compares with the current 10 a.m.-12:30 p.m. and 2:30
p.m.-4 p.m. sessions.  Trading hours will be further extended, with the lunch
break being cut further to one hour from 1.5 hours from March 5,
2012, the bourse said in an e-mailed statement. From that date,
markets will reopen after the lunch break at 1 p.m., according
to the statement sent after a meeting of the exchange’s board
members today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Hanny Wan  in Hong Kong at 
 hwan3@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
